1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:06,000
National Radio and Television Administration

2
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,160
Go and get some rest.

3
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,600
Is that Huaming?

4
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:08,919
Xinxin, I don't think you need to be like this.

5
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:12,160
There's nothing wrong with him liking you.

6
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:13,960
I just feel that

7
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,400
I went a bit too far today.

8
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,760
No, this has nothing to do with you.

9
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,540
You did nothing wrong.

10
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,360
Ah.

11
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,020
You must never get so worked up again.

12
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:29,610
We're lucky nothing serious happened today.

13
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:30,960
Don't worry.

14
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,280
Huaming won't come around anymore

15
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,600
to disturb our lives.

16
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:36,680
Xiaogan and I will always take care of you.

17
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:49,440
Xinxin, I've been waiting so long to hear you say that.

18
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:55,040
Could you stop calling me auntie from now on?

19
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:01,960
Mom.

20
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,600
Xiaogan.

21
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:18,400
Quickly, call the lawyer

22
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,530
and tell him to come here right now.

23
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,130
I want to change my will.

24
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,520
Mom, focus on getting better first.

25
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,360
This can wait. Don't rush.

26
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,240
No.

27
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:35,760
Although I know my own body well,

28
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,920
today was really too close a call.

29
00:03:39,079 --> 00:03:41,800
What if one day I can't catch my breath

30
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,010
what will happen to you two?

31
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,160
What about my grandson?

32
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,760
Mom, you...

33
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,890
Please don't say such unlucky things.

34
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:54,400
Okay, Mom. I'll call right away,

35
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,120
but it's so late now.

36
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,800
I'll ask him to come first thing tomorrow.

37
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,520
No.

38
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:01,960
He must come immediately, right now.

39
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,640
Go quickly.

40
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:09,720
Okay.

41
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,680
Hello?

42
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,940
We're about to see the light at the end of the tunnel.

43
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,460
What are you doing?

44
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:47,120
You scared me to death!

45
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,650
I thought you were Qin Gang.

46
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:52,220
Why are you still hanging around here? Let's go.

47
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,159
What's wrong?

48
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,360
Look, it's almost 5 o'clock now.

49
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,280
That bastard will definitely go find Liu Wei after work.

50
00:04:58,280 --> 00:04:58,960
Brother, don't worry.

51
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,760
This time I'll definitely get photos of them together.

52
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:03,160
We'll wipe away our previous humiliation.

53
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,120
Learn from your mistakes.

54
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,960
He knows we've photographed him before.

55
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:10,640
Would he stay here and let you take pictures freely?

56
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,200
Wait, what does that mean?

57
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,120
Give up?

58
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:15,560
Who said anything about giving up? This is a strategic retreat.

59
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,920
We'll let him lower his guard.

60
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,480
Make him think the danger is gone.

61
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,080
Then he'll slip up on his own.

62
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,640
Let's go.

63
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,040
Just like that?

64
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:26,680
What's wrong?

65
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,960
Here he comes!

66
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,360
Hey!

67
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,240
Hey, Xinxin.

68
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,040
How's my mom doing?

69
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,920
She's much better today.

70
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,720
I'm planning to take her out for a walk this afternoon.

71
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,040
What would you like to eat?

72
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:48,400
I'm fine with anything.

73
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:49,880
Hold on a second.

74
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,159
Dr. Hua.

75
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:55,040
Dr. Hua, where are you?

76
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,920
He's at the company.

77
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,720
At the company entrance?

78
00:05:58,760 --> 00:05:59,880
Why is he there?

79
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,880
Now Dr. Hua and Xu Ke...

80
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,680
He's my knight in shining armor.

81
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,400
Yes.

82
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:09,520
He takes me to work on time.

83
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,040
And waits for me after work.

84
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,640
Put him on the phone.

85
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,120
Don't be angry.

86
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:20,320
There might be a misunderstanding between Dr. Hua and me.

87
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,800
We just need to clear things up.

88
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,640
Don't let my mom know.

89
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,640
Her blood pressure will spike again.

90
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,120
I'll go buy seafood now.

91
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,650
Wait for me to come back.

92
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,040
Alright, bye-bye.

93
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,240
Dr. Hua.

94
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,240
Why are you giving me such a hard time?

95
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:42,520
Permission.

96
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,920
Why are you here?

97
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,240
I'm... taking portrait photos.

98
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,080
No, actually...

99
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,400
I want to buy a new car.

100
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,920
Right, this dealership is for buying cars.

101
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,600
But you...

102
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,360
Can you afford such a nice car?

103
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,170
Is it expensive?

104
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,480
I think it's affordable.

105
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,960
The car is nice, but this dealership...

106
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,820
And this person...

107
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,120
Not so great.

108
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,400
I'm asking if you can afford it.

109
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,320
If I can't, I'll borrow money from you.

110
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,000
Fine, I'll lend you some. Let's go.

111
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,260
Let's go get the money.

112
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,360
Let's go.

113
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,320
Wait.

114
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:18,800
Dr. Hua.

115
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,920
I'm warning you.

116
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:23,600
If you...

117
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,200
keep interfering with my life like this,

118
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,800
I won't be so polite anymore.

119
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,600
You don't stand a chance.

120
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,760
You can't beat him.

121
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:35,880
Ming.

122
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,120
Xinxin.

123
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:47,920
Mom.

124
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,640
Why are you up?

125
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,040
Where's Bao?

126
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,490
He just fell asleep.

127
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:53,920
That's why I came down.

128
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,720
Come, sit for a while.

129
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,840
Why don't you rest a bit longer?

130
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,920
What's the point of lying down?

131
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:05,040
This is my old condition. I know what's happening.

132
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,360
Someone like me

133
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,600
might not make it through one day.

134
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,440
That's just how it is.

135
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,860
Auntie, that's not even considered an illness.

136
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,240
Didn't the doctor say

137
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,200
you should stay happy

138
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,280
and keep your blood pressure stable?

139
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,680
The key is to avoid getting emotional.

140
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,810
Then you'll be fine.

141
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,000
I know.

142
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,720
By the way, that medication I've been taking,

143
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:34,960
the blood pressure medicine prescribed by the doctor here.

144
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:35,960
Ni...

145
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,360
Nifedipine.

146
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:40,760
It's similar to what I took in America.

147
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,720
Works very well.

148
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:42,760
That's great!

149
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,920
But you can't just rely on medication.

150
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:47,720
You need to regulate yourself and stay in a good mood.

151
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,320
Of course I'm happy.

152
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,360
You and the baby are back.

153
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,120
Our family is reunited.

154
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,720
I have no reason not to be happy.

155
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,720
As long as that Huaming doesn't come to cause trouble,

156
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:01,450
I absolutely won't have anything to worry about.

157
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,000
Auntie, when the baby wakes up later,

158
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,200
could you look after him for me?

159
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,120
I need to go out for a bit. I'll be back soon.

160
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,250
Where are you going?

161
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,520
I'm going to buy some things. I'll be back shortly.

162
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,160
Okay.

163
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,420
So you still remember to come find me.

164
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:37,240
I've got this big problem I can't shake off.

165
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,240
That Hua Ming is really determined to fight me.

166
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,640
He wants to challenge me.

167
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,280
He really thinks he's somebody important.

168
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,880
When will this ever end?

169
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,040
Don't worry. Soon.

170
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,000
I met with the lawyer today.

171
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,730
I'll be taking over the family business soon.

172
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,720
Soon, soon. You always say soon.

173
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:00,280
I can't just stay at home all day like this.

174
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,480
It's suffocating.

175
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,640
I have a pile of work at my company.

176
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:05,680
I can only handle everything remotely by phone.

177
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:08,400
What will happen to my magazine if this continues?

178
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,360
Forget the magazine, I need you.

179
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,000
The family business is huge.

180
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,000
I need someone to help me, right?

181
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:16,040
If it weren't for that troublemaker Hua Ming,

182
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,480
making my mother sick with anger,

183
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,740
all this would have been resolved by now.

184
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,880
But you can't just let him

185
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,680
keep causing trouble like this.

186
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,280
What can I do? We live in a society with laws.

187
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:27,600
I can't exactly challenge him to a duel, can I?

188
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,600
We need to think of a long-term plan.

189
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,420
Let me think of a solution for you.

190
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,040
What's your idea?

191
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,490
Make him disappear for a while.

192
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:40,540
Then no one will be causing you trouble anymore.

193
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,680
Why are you back?

194
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:10,100
Have you eaten? I'll make you something.

195
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,780
Watch some TV. I'll be done cooking soon.

196
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,380
What exactly are you trying to do?

197
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:24,840
What's wrong?

198
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,500
Are you still pretending to be clueless?

199
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,880
You were the one who told me to move back.

200
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,760
The Qin family is wealthy and powerful.

201
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,240
After your brother returns to the Qin family,

202
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,360
he'll get a better education.

203
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,480
Really, it's a good thing.

204
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,760
I finally accepted him

205
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,000
I was living with his family

206
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,560
and starting a new life.

207
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,080
Now that I've gone back home,

208
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,920
you keep going there causing trouble.

209
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:06,780
What exactly are you trying to do?

210
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,730
I think something's wrong.

211
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,980
What do you think is wrong?

212
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,680
Ever since that incident at the car dealership,

213
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,080
you've been saying something's wrong.

214
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,280
That the whole situation is suspicious.

215
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:20,880
If there's a problem, why don't you just say it?

216
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:22,880
I don't know.

217
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,370
I just feel something's not right.

218
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,720
Are you okay?

219
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,200
You're a grown man, yet you go there making scenes every day.

220
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,080
Don't you know that Mrs. Qin

221
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:32,680
has been hospitalized?

222
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,040
Do you want her to die from anger?

223
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,420
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

224
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,280
I won't go to their house anymore.

225
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,160
I hope in the future

226
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,160
you'll stop disrupting my life too.

227
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:52,880
This is my choice.

228
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,400
I won't regret it.

229
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,840
I regret it.

230
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:03,520
I'm telling you I regret persuading you to go back.

231
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,920
I want you to move back in with me.

232
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,280
You regret it?

233
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:19,200
Saying this now, don't you think

234
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,840
you're being ridiculous?

235
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,040
What do you think I am?

236
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,480
Someone you can summon and dismiss at will?

237
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:33,440
What's the point of saying this now?

238
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,080
Xinxin.

239
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,120
Everything I've done

240
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,800
was to help you and Bao.

241
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,480
I came here today to tell you

242
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,000
I've decided to remarry Qin Gang.

243
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,640
Are you sure?

244
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,760
Yes, I am.

245
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,840
Don't you want to say something?

246
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,480
No.

247
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,120
Fine.

248
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,280
I know you're a good person.

249
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,290
You've been good to both me and Bao.

250
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,680
But I can never figure you out.

251
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,760
I never know

252
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,000
what you're really thinking inside.

253
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,480
That door of yours is always closed to me.

254
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,960
I can never open it.

255
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,920
It's not just me. Any woman

256
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,240
would feel insecure.

257
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,960
Can't you change?

258
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,640
Wan Xinxin.

259
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,400
Since I met you,

260
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:11,920
I've changed a lot.

261
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:20,580
Then I guess I don't know you well enough.

262
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:27,170
Or maybe I'm just not the right person for you.

263
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,520
I hope

264
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,570
you find the right person someday.

265
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,480
Let me nibble those little feet.

266
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,120
Look at those tiny feet.

267
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:34,960
Look at him.

268
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,560
So handsome and beautiful at such a young age.

269
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,000
He's little Xiao Gang now.

270
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,320
When he grows up, he'll be big Xiao Gang.

271
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:46,720
Mom, when Xiaobao starts elementary school,

272
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,580
we should send him to America.

273
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:51,640
Why? Why send him away so young?

274
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,880
You haven't lived abroad, so you don't understand.

275
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,480
The whole world is looking to China now.

276
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:59,240
Everyone is learning Chinese.

277
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,720
He must go to school here.

278
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,319
When he grows up, it will be his own choice.

279
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:07,480
